Technological determinism is a term that encompasses a wide range of ideas in practice, from technological push or technological imperative to a strict sense that human destiny is driven by underlying logic associated with scientific laws and their manifestation in technology.
Many interpretations of technological deterrence share two general ideas: that the development of technology itself follows a course largely beyond cultural or political influence, and that technology, in turn, has effects" on societies that are inherent, rather than socially conditioned.
For example, it can be said that cars necessarily lead to the development of roads.
